SIMPLE: unballasted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unballasted
<hw>Un*bal"last*ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[Properly p. p.
of <ets>unballast</ets>.]</ety> <def>Freed from ballast; having
discharged ballast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>ballasted</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not furnished with ballast; not kept
steady by ballast; unsteady; <as>as, <ex>unballasted</ex> vessels;
<ex>unballasted</ex> wits</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Unballasted</qex> by any sufficient weight of plan.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbanded</ent>⟦br⟧
